Back in 2018, Fox News’ Tucker Carlson was full of indignation after “Saturday Night Live” comedian Pete Davidson poked fun at Rep. Dan Crenshaw’s (R-Texas) eye patch, which the congressman has worn since sustaining an injury on active military service in Afghanistan. Now? Not so much. This week, Carlson called former Navy SEAL Crenshaw “eye patch McCain” after the lawmaker said sending military aid to Ukraine amid the Russia invasion has nothing to do with the U.S. baby formula shortage. Carlson’s dig referenced the late Sen. John McCain (R-Ariz.), who also sustained long-term injury during war service. “You hurl juvenile insults when you know you’ve lost the debate,” Crenshaw said in response to Carlson’s attack. Progressive PAC MeidasTouch cut Carlson’s comments together on Tuesday, and the evidence of the blowhard’s hypocrisy is now going viral: